<br>
Of course, you need to exercise some common sense.  <br>
<br>
Let's say for instance that the pally book dropped off Naggy and there was no paladin there, but there was a paladin in the zone, I would much rather it go to the paladin in the zone and not in the raid than give it to another class.  <br>
<br>
This allows the class who needs the book to have the book, but of course does not benefit anyone in the raid directly.<br>
<br>
The raid got the bonus of killing the mob, which as always imo is the most important thing - not what they drop.  I do not kill singular mobs for their loot (really), I do it for knowledge mroe than anything.  <br>
<br>
The exceptions to this are the zone hits.<br>
<br>
But the raid leader can basically do what they like in the best part.  Whether they changed the loot rules or not, as long as it does not directly benefit themselves, they are free to change rules whereever.  <br>
<br>
The rules I have run during FFA is random 200 NBG and raid leader has ultimate decisions on loot.  If someone is not happy about this fuck'em.  There are other people that will be, as long as they put their confidence and trust in the raid leader.  <br>
<br>
I rarely had a problem with FFA raids at all, but had plenty of experience with them and people entrusted me to run these raids which were in the best part 90%+ successful.<br>
<br>
Any person during these raids who were not happy with decisions were free to leave at any time.  <br>
<br>
Of course, though even raid leaders make snap decisions which are wrong - we are not infallable....so understanding is key from the raiders also. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raluvinssteele>Raluvin Ssteele</A> at: 1/7/03 5:15:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=galianaohmsford>Galiana Ohmsford</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tolapumj wanna-be</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(1/7/03 3:31:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=763.topic&index=73>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  &gt; Re: Cheatch Learn to run a raid.</span><hr size=1> The idea of calling someone in to roll on an item when he wasn't there to take the risk and contribute DPS on a dragon raid, OVER a guy who was there, is lame and stupid. I would raise all hell if a raid leader tried to pull that, even if it wasn't something I'd want to roll on. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :flame --><img src=http://smilies.networkessence.net/s/otn/angry/pain10.gif ALT=":flame"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That pally was there, he put in the effort. He deserved it.<br>
